Text:
This year too, the beginning of the New Year is upon
us! It's the 3rd Great Ize-eathlon!
"This year too" kind of indicates a short history...

Now for the three ascetic exercises passed down at
Great Ize Shrine! They have been greatly changed
for an open competition!

For those with the amazing luck to get the most
points, you will receive specially made kagami
rice cakes!

The kagami rice cakes Boss man wants! Right, we gotta
win this!

Well, when it comes to physical strength you're in
a league of your own, Delta.
I will enter too, but I will take it easy...

Now, without further ado, the first contestâ€•The
"Great Ize Fortune Dash"!

Contestants start from the big gate at the front of
the shrine! The goal is the mega rice cake at the
back of the shrine!

It's just a simple footrace. If that's the case, then
Delta is enough.

In that mega rice cake, you'll find many
fortune slips!
Huh?

Whoever can find the fortune slip for "Great
Fortune" first will be the winner!

We need speed and luck... So I do actually need to
get involved...

All participants, please go around to the big gate in
front of the shrine!
...Huh? Oh dear! Delta, let's go!
Huh? What's the hurry...?
Wow, so many people! I can't even see the start gate!

Beaten before we even began... The contest had
started before the rules were explained.

The win goes to whoever gets to the start point
first... We should have gone to the gate as soon as
we entered, without waiting for the explanation.

So this means we're gonna start from a long way
behind.
Meanwhile, the leading group can run pretty freely.

I was too careless. I thought it would be easy to get
kagami rice cake and take it home to Cid!

We can still win! This is just a handicap that makes
it fair for the rest of 'em!
Delta...
I'm gonna take them all out and get to first place!

...You're right, complaining about it here achieves
nothing.

Then let's get this started! In your positions!
Ready...
START!
Yaaaaaa!!!

Urk... The frontrunners are blocking the way!
We can't even start running.
To the front!!!
Delta!

(Even in the middle of this crowd, she is running at
tremendous speed, weaving in and out...!)

(Only a therianathrope can run like that... No, only
Delta can run like that!)
You're in my way! Move, move!
Whaâ€”! Stop pushing!
Ack, aaah! I'm gonna fall in!!!
Fall in...? Look at that, a hole opened up!

Gahhh!!! Hope those are just New Yearâ€™s bamboo
decorations!!!

(There are sharp bamboo sticks at the bottom of the
hole... Ouch, that's gotta hurt.)
You gotta jump over the pitfalls!

Arrgghh! There are arrows hitting the landing point!
We can't avoid them!!!

(Cool! So many red and white arrows flying around
when you jump!)
Aroo!

(You gotta land and roll forward! Then roll onto all
fours and keep your footing!)

What theâ€•! That dog! She is avoiding all of the rapid
fire ceremonial arrows!
Move, move! Today is Delta's day!
Huh? The runners at the back have already caught up?!
How are they keeping up...?
Where's the giant rice cake at?! There!
Grr... We haven't lost yet!
We gotta find the "Great Fortune" slip first!
*munch, munch, munch*
She's not even digging. She's eating the rice cake!!!
That's nuts! She'll eat the fortune slips!
Ptooey! I bit into something!
Nooo, she spat out a fortune slip!
Erm, what's this, errrr... "G-R-E-A-T"...
Damn! She got the "Great Fortune" slip!
"Great radish!"
I can still find it!
Another fortune slip! "Poof!"
"Try again!"
"Cat!"

*sigh* There's the lead group. I wonder how Delta is
doing.
"Great King!" "Lucky Later!" "Very Lucky Later!"
Don't tell me... They still haven't dug it out?!
No! Ahh! "Hit! One more try!"

What does "hit" even mean...? Come on, you need to
search properly. If you hold it up to the light, you
can see through it.

Oh, it's see-through! But there are so many letters,
so it's not "Great Fortune!"
I got something!
You guys...
"Great Cat!" "Great Fortune!" "Great Trouble!"
Huh? Did you just say...
I got it! "Great Fortune!" I'm the winnâ€•
GIVE IT TO ME!!!
Guargh!
I got the "Great Fortune" fortune slip!

You just hit him really hard and took it. That has to
be against the rules...

And there you have it! In the end, all therianthropes
solve problems through force! The win goes to the
canine therianthrope Delta!
Yay! I won! I'm the winner!
Seriously? What is it with therianathropes...?
